;; Graphic defs, loaded by sim.defs into (:graphic db). Content, not code.
;; A graphic names ONE base source: a sheet :cell [sheet col row] (water keeps
;; this, with :anim) or an :image path to a loose PNG (everything else, sliced
;; from 32rogues by dev/tools/slice_sprites.clj). Optional :draw-size/:draw-offset
;; (tile units, default [1 1]/[0 0]) decouple sprite size from the tile footprint.
;; :directional marks a pawn-style Graphic_Multi; :facings (absent for now)
;; overrides per direction, with :right defaulting to a horizontal flip of :left.
{:grass    {:image "graphics/grass.png"}
 :dirt     {:image "graphics/dirt.png"}
 :gravel   {:image "graphics/gravel.png"}
 :stone    {:image "graphics/stone.png"}
 :wall     {:image "graphics/wall.png"}
 ;; A hand-made door sprite, authored as a text grid in sim.render.pixel-art and
 ;; generated to graphics/door.png (run (pixel-art/regenerate!) after editing the
 ;; grid). Swapping in art is a one-line :image change, exactly why the graphic is
 ;; a content ref, no code touched.
 :door     {:image "graphics/door.png"}
 :water    {:cell [:animated 0 10] :anim {:frames 11 :fps 6}}
 :colonist {:image "graphics/colonist.png" :directional true}
 :tree     {:image "graphics/tree.png"}
 :wood     {:image "graphics/wood.png"}
 :rock     {:image "graphics/rock.png"}
 :apple    {:image "graphics/apple.png"}}
